   <remark>
    <p>
        The previous activities illustrate that, in the case when <m>f(x)</m> is describing the instantaneous change of some quantity, then the definite integral <m>\int_a^b f(x)dx</m> describes the <alert>net change</alert> of this quantity over the interval <m>[a,b]</m>. 
    </p>
   </remark>
    
